               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors; incipit of each commemorative notice; the word sälam "salutation"; a few other words (e.g., fols. 3rb, 114vbc, 116rc, 206vc); elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation signs (e.g., nine dot asterisks and chains of red and black dots separating the commemorative notices: fols. 57vbc, 101rbc, 149vabc, 203vabc, 260vabc; chains of red and black dots separating the days: e.g., fols. 72vb, 184ra; nine dot asterisks: e.g., fols. 7rc, 20ra, 33ra, 71vc, 181va, 236ra, 298ra).&#xD;
&#xD;
Several lines or groups of lines on the page opening the commemorative notices for each month are rubricated: 3 red lines alternating with black lines, 2 red lines below (fols. 3r, 58r, 101v, 150r, 203r, 260v).</rubric>
